{
"explanation": "In determining the sentence, the court acknowledges the defendant's status as a first-time offender and the mitigating factor that partial restitution has already been made, which indicates a degree of remorse and an effort to rectify the harm caused. However, as an accountant, the defendant occupied a position of trust and had a professional obligation to maintain financial integrity. The embezzlement of $25,000 for personal gain constitutes an abuse of that fiduciary responsibility. A 9-month term of incarceration is appropriate to reflect the seriousness of the breach of trust and to serve as a deterrent against similar white-collar crimes, while also providing weight to the defendant's clean prior record and voluntary repayment efforts.",
"verdict": 9
}
